> All hail this low-carb, quick-to-the-table lunch idea! It's light, creamy, and
> full of texture, flavor, and crunch. You'll dice up tender pre-cooked chicken
> and combine it with crispy croutons, Parm, and chopped lettuce, then dress it
> in a creamy, savory Caesar dressing and wrap it in baby romaine lettuce
> leaves. It's a lunchtime coup the likes of which Brutus would be proud.

Wash and dry produce. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate
leaves. Roughly chop small center leaves. Pat @fully cooked chicken breasts{8.6%ounce} dry with
#paper towels{}; dice into ½-inch pieces. Lightly crush @croutons{1} in their
bag using the bottom of a #mug{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @Caesar dressing{1.5%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon},
and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir chopped lettuce, chicken, and half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} into
bowl with creamy dressing; toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide lettuce leaves between plates; fill with chicken salad. Top with
croutons and remaining Parmesan. Serve.